    <thetext>Description of problem:
xfce4-pulseaudio-plugin&apos;s mixer menu requires pavucontrol.
The error message might confuse newbies/newcomers, so I think the pavucontrol package should be a dependency of xfce4-pulseaudio-plugin.

Version-Release number of selected component (if applicable):
xfce4-pulseaudio-plugin-0.2.5-1.fc26.i686.rpm

How reproducible:
Always

Steps to Reproduce:
1. Right click on the audio mixer icon
2. Select the option &quot;Audio mixer&quot; (mine is an Italian system, so the exact spelling may vary)

Actual results:
1. The system states that the &quot;pavucontrol&quot; command is not found.

Expected results:
1. Ideally, xfce4-pulseaudio-plugin should provide everything &quot;out-of-the-box&quot;.

Additional info:
Installing pavucontrol fixes this little issue.</thetext>
